    <h2>ðŸ§ª Types of Soil</h2>

    <div class="soil-type">
      <h3>1. Loamy Soil</h3>
      <p>Rich in nutrients and holds moisture well. Best for most crops.</p>
      <strong>Ideal Plants:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Wheat</li>
        <li>Sugarcane</li>
        <li>Vegetables (Tomato, Carrot)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="soil-type">
      <h3>2. Sandy Soil</h3>
      <p>Drains quickly and is low in nutrients.</p>
      <strong>Ideal Plants:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Watermelon</li>
        <li>Peanuts</li>
        <li>Potatoes</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="soil-type">
      <h3>3. Clayey Soil</h3>
      <p>Retains water, dense and sticky.</p>
      <strong>Ideal Plants:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Rice</li>
        <li>Broccoli</li>
        <li>Sunflower</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

